WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:15.000
Downloaded From AnimeArcadia.lk

00:06.855 --> 00:08.855
[unearthly, distressing music playing]

00:10.438 --> 00:11.438
[energy crackling]

00:22.313 --> 00:23.313
[wind rushing]

00:36.521 --> 00:37.605
[groaning weakly]

00:37.688 --> 00:39.938
[gagging, coughing]

00:40.021 --> 00:41.188
[raspy breathing]

00:47.896 --> 00:49.896
[breathing evens out]

01:05.563 --> 01:10.230
As meeting places go, this spot suits you.

01:10.313 --> 01:11.438
You may try to hide it,

01:11.521 --> 01:14.313
but you've got as much of a flair
for the dramatic as I do.

01:14.938 --> 01:15.896
See?

01:16.521 --> 01:18.896
[horned demon] You have it? All of it.

01:19.396 --> 01:20.855
Your information was right.

01:20.938 --> 01:23.271
Dante is the son of Sparda.

01:23.355 --> 01:26.396
His necklace fit very nicely
with the one you gave me.

01:27.355 --> 01:29.146
I held up my end.

01:29.230 --> 01:31.771
All I need now is the final piece.

01:31.855 --> 01:33.438
As promised.

01:36.230 --> 01:38.646
[tense music crescendoing]

01:41.230 --> 01:42.230
[music halts]

01:42.771 --> 01:44.896
[energy surging, whooshing]

01:50.313 --> 01:51.813
[smugly] Uh-huh…

01:54.813 --> 01:56.813
Well, I'd say that's good enough.

01:59.396 --> 02:01.771
The blood of Sparda's other son.

02:02.271 --> 02:04.855
You never know
what will turn up in this realm.

02:05.480 --> 02:08.563
It takes both brothers
to destroy the barrier.

02:08.646 --> 02:11.938
Oh, don't worry.
I'm already working on completing the set.

02:14.771 --> 02:16.438
[energy thrumming]

02:19.188 --> 02:20.188
This sword…

02:20.688 --> 02:24.188
Far too great a power
for one like you to wield.

02:24.896 --> 02:26.105
Maybe so.

02:26.605 --> 02:31.105
But seeing as I'm about to use that power
to undo the historic crime of its maker

02:31.188 --> 02:33.271
and free every Makaian from our bondage,

02:34.605 --> 02:37.063
how about I hold onto it for a while?

02:37.146 --> 02:38.730
[energy resonating]

02:39.438 --> 02:41.063
I know who you are.

02:41.646 --> 02:42.938
[restrained growl]

02:43.021 --> 02:47.396
There's only one way you could have
gotten the amulet piece and this blood.

02:48.396 --> 02:50.396
[dark, overwhelming synth music playing]

02:52.563 --> 02:54.563
[White Rabbit cackling]

03:04.021 --> 03:05.480
[growls]

03:09.688 --> 03:11.188
Prepare yourselves!

03:13.230 --> 03:14.688
Dante's coming.

03:15.605 --> 03:16.605
[music trails off]

03:22.730 --> 03:24.730
["Rollin' (Air Raid Vehicle)"
by Limp Bizkit playing]

03:24.813 --> 03:26.980
♪ Your… your… your hands up ♪

03:27.063 --> 03:29.730
♪ Your… your… your hands up ♪

03:29.813 --> 03:32.480
♪ Throw your hands up
Throw your hands up ♪

03:32.563 --> 03:34.980
♪ Move in, now move out
Hands up, now hands down ♪

03:35.063 --> 03:37.646
♪ Back up, back up
Tell me what you're gonna do now ♪

03:37.730 --> 03:40.355
♪ Breathe in, now breathe out
Hands up, now hands down ♪

03:40.438 --> 03:42.521
♪ Back up, back up
Tell me what you're gonna do now ♪

03:42.605 --> 03:45.313
♪ Keep rollin', rollin'
Rollin', rollin' ♪

03:45.396 --> 03:47.730
♪ Keep rollin', rollin'
Rollin', rollin' ♪

03:47.813 --> 03:50.230
♪ Keep rollin', rollin'
Rollin', rollin' ♪

03:50.313 --> 03:52.730
♪ Keep rollin', rollin'
Rollin', rollin' ♪

03:52.813 --> 03:54.938
♪ Hey, ladies, hey, fellas ♪

03:55.021 --> 03:57.813
♪ And the people that don't give a **** ♪

03:57.896 --> 03:59.980
♪ All the lovers, all the haters ♪

04:00.063 --> 04:02.813
♪ And all the people
That call themselves players ♪

04:02.896 --> 04:04.896
♪ Hot mommas, pimp daddies ♪

04:04.980 --> 04:07.896
♪ And the people rollin' up in Caddies ♪

04:07.980 --> 04:10.396
♪ Hey, rockers, hip-hoppers ♪

04:10.480 --> 04:12.646
♪ And everybody all around the world ♪

04:12.730 --> 04:15.396
♪ Move in, now move out
Hands up, now hands down ♪

04:15.480 --> 04:17.896
♪ Back up, back up
Tell me what you're gonna do now ♪

04:17.980 --> 04:20.105
♪ Breathe in, now breathe out
Hands up, now hands down ♪

04:20.188 --> 04:22.980
♪ Back up, back up
Tell me what you're gonna do now ♪

04:23.063 --> 04:25.188
♪ Keep rollin'
Rollin', rollin', rollin' ♪

04:25.271 --> 04:27.771
♪ Keep rollin'
Rollin', rollin', rollin' ♪

04:27.855 --> 04:30.480
♪ Keep rollin'
Rollin', rollin', rollin' ♪

04:30.563 --> 04:31.563
[song trails off]

04:38.605 --> 04:39.480
[groans]

04:39.563 --> 04:41.230
[coughing]

04:44.355 --> 04:45.855
[groans breathily]

04:50.438 --> 04:52.438
You threw me through a fucking window!

04:52.521 --> 04:55.896
In a dashing act of heroics
that saved you from certain death.

04:55.980 --> 04:57.396
That part seems important.

04:57.480 --> 04:59.355
Spare me the jack-off session.

04:59.438 --> 05:01.146
I would have got out on my…

05:01.230 --> 05:02.230
[gasps]

05:14.813 --> 05:15.771
Lady.

05:16.313 --> 05:18.271
I know. They're gone.

05:19.355 --> 05:21.021
Not just my people.

05:21.105 --> 05:22.105
His too.

05:23.521 --> 05:27.271
He'll stack as many corpses as he needs
to prop the door to Hell open.

05:37.063 --> 05:38.813
Where are you going?

05:39.396 --> 05:42.646
To stop the Rabbit and beat
little pellets of shit down his leg.

05:42.730 --> 05:44.938
[Dante] No. He told me to come alone.

05:45.605 --> 05:47.771
And you're actually gonna listen to him?

05:48.480 --> 05:51.688
Before today,
maybe I tried not to think about it.

05:51.771 --> 05:55.063
Because if I had the idea of having
anything in common with a demon…

05:55.146 --> 05:56.521
When it was their kind who…

05:57.021 --> 05:59.230
But Sparda, he was different.

05:59.313 --> 06:00.313
Him being my father,

06:00.396 --> 06:03.313
I thought the demon side
of me would be different too.

06:03.396 --> 06:04.563
Then it came out.

06:05.063 --> 06:07.813
Turning demon showed me
what my power really is.

06:07.896 --> 06:11.438
Forced me to feel the rage
and hatred that feeds it.

06:12.938 --> 06:14.605
Rage and hatred?

06:14.688 --> 06:15.896
Sounds about right.

06:16.396 --> 06:20.855
Sparda, my dad,
he must have felt the same thing.

06:20.938 --> 06:22.688
But he found a way to fight it,

06:22.771 --> 06:25.730
to turn his power back
against the darkness it came from.

06:25.813 --> 06:28.105
He created the wall
that protects this world.

06:28.813 --> 06:31.480
It was his amulet
my mom gave me to keep safe.

06:32.271 --> 06:34.396
Now the Rabbit is about to use that amulet

06:34.480 --> 06:37.480
to tear the wall to pieces
and let all of Hell walk through.

06:39.105 --> 06:40.938
I have to be the one who stops him.

06:42.646 --> 06:44.355
Yeah, fuck that.

06:45.355 --> 06:46.688
[Dante groans]

06:46.771 --> 06:48.521
You shot my leg!

06:48.605 --> 06:50.396
Why would you shoot my leg?

06:50.480 --> 06:51.771
As a courtesy.

06:51.855 --> 06:54.021
Otherwise, it would have been
between your eyes.

06:54.605 --> 06:55.855
[Dante grunts]

06:55.938 --> 06:57.188
[Mary] I mean, seriously?

06:57.771 --> 07:00.438
Your blood is the exact
fucking thing the Rabbit needs

07:00.521 --> 07:02.021
to jumpstart his apocalypse,

07:02.105 --> 07:03.521
you demonic dumbass.

07:04.313 --> 07:06.021
And this isn't about your dad.

07:06.105 --> 07:09.438
It's about whatever fucked up vendetta
the Rabbit has against DARKCOM.

07:09.521 --> 07:12.105
Which means it's my fight.

07:13.396 --> 07:15.855
Ah, well that makes me feel way better!

07:16.730 --> 07:17.980
I'm going in myself.

07:22.521 --> 07:25.230
["Butterfly" by Crazy Town playing]

07:25.313 --> 07:27.480
[funky, melodic rock/hip-hop playing]

07:27.563 --> 07:28.605
♪ You're my pretty baby ♪

07:28.688 --> 07:31.146
♪ I'll make your legs shake
You make me go crazy ♪

07:31.230 --> 07:33.355
♪ Come my lady, come, come my lady ♪

07:33.438 --> 07:35.521
♪ You're my butterfly, sugar baby ♪

07:35.605 --> 07:37.980
Hey baby, you need a ride?

07:38.063 --> 07:40.646
Because I definitely
need you to ride this dick--

07:40.730 --> 07:41.771
[gagging]

07:41.855 --> 07:44.271
[forcefully] Out of the car, now!

07:44.771 --> 07:45.813
[engine revving]

07:45.896 --> 07:48.396
♪ Come and dance with me
Come and dance with me ♪

07:48.480 --> 07:49.980
♪ Uh-huh, uh-huh ♪

07:50.480 --> 07:53.146
♪ Come and dance with me
Come and dance with me ♪

07:53.688 --> 07:55.230
[buzzing]

07:55.313 --> 07:57.480
[taut, suspenseful music playing]

08:00.021 --> 08:03.105
I did everything you asked. We're done.

08:03.688 --> 08:04.855
[White Rabbit] You did.

08:04.938 --> 08:07.938
An obedient soldier, through and through.

08:08.021 --> 08:12.563
Unfortunately,
I've hit a snag in my final plan.

08:13.146 --> 08:14.146
[line disconnects]

08:16.813 --> 08:17.771
Steady!

08:18.480 --> 08:20.271
The traitor's spawn is almost here.

08:20.355 --> 08:22.980
Remember, you just have to land one blow.

08:24.730 --> 08:25.813
He'll come.

08:29.563 --> 08:30.813
[grumbles]

08:30.896 --> 08:32.646
[demons snarling]

08:33.230 --> 08:34.230
[White Rabbit] Hmm.

08:38.688 --> 08:39.688
[growls]

08:40.230 --> 08:42.063
-We attack now.
-[White Rabbit] Wait!

08:44.521 --> 08:46.355
-He will come.
-[engine revving in distance]

08:52.730 --> 08:54.730
[energetic industrial music building]

08:58.396 --> 08:59.605
Bloodstryke!

09:07.605 --> 09:09.646
Sorry, it's not personal.

09:17.521 --> 09:19.063
[bellows]

09:27.521 --> 09:28.355
[engine revving]

09:29.188 --> 09:30.438
[horns honking]

09:52.771 --> 09:53.646
[splat]

09:57.605 --> 09:59.021
[Mary] Who'd you expect?

10:00.355 --> 10:02.646
Some dickhead
in a musty leather trench coat?

10:02.730 --> 10:03.730
[White Rabbit chuckles]

10:04.605 --> 10:05.855
Arkham.

10:05.938 --> 10:07.438
Nice trade.

10:07.521 --> 10:08.938
But you're out of cars.

10:09.021 --> 10:11.313
And I've got a lot more warriors.

10:12.438 --> 10:13.563
[Mary] Lucky for them,

10:14.563 --> 10:16.063
I'm here to negotiate.

10:18.438 --> 10:20.771
With what, exactly?

10:21.355 --> 10:23.063
Dante's life.

10:23.146 --> 10:24.855
I press this button,

10:24.938 --> 10:27.771
and the most irritating member
of both our species

10:27.855 --> 10:30.063
gets turned to a fucking cinder.

10:30.563 --> 10:33.855
Might be hard to take
a DNA sample from him after that.

10:33.938 --> 10:34.938
I see.

10:35.855 --> 10:38.855
So, in exchange for
not eradicating my blood supply,

10:38.938 --> 10:41.021
you want me to call off the attack.

10:41.105 --> 10:42.563
And give me the amulet.

10:42.646 --> 10:43.813
[White Rabbit guffawing]

10:44.396 --> 10:48.021
How do you fit those balls
in that skintight uniform?

10:48.105 --> 10:50.521
Laugh your fucking cottonpuff tail off,

10:50.605 --> 10:53.355
but if Dante burns, his blood is gone.

10:53.438 --> 10:54.355
Forever.

10:55.355 --> 10:57.771
You put these demons through torture,

10:57.855 --> 11:01.021
fucked with their genetic codes,
all for your cause.

11:01.521 --> 11:04.813
You should take the deal
to keep the hope for the cause alive.

11:05.813 --> 11:08.646
Unless you have another agenda
they should know about.

11:14.813 --> 11:15.813
Take it.

11:19.938 --> 11:21.980
A pleasure, as always.

11:22.896 --> 11:24.938
Aren't you forgetting something?

11:26.021 --> 11:27.813
If this wasn't just a bluff,

11:28.480 --> 11:31.771
if you really had Dante
locked up somewhere,

11:32.271 --> 11:35.521
you would have incinerated him
the second I gave you that.

11:36.105 --> 11:39.938
Don't tell me
you've grown fond of the half-breed.

11:40.021 --> 11:41.688
Not fucking likely.

11:42.271 --> 11:43.188
["Butterfly" playing]

11:43.271 --> 11:44.980
♪ So come and dance with me, uh-huh ♪

11:45.063 --> 11:46.063
[horde wincing]

11:46.146 --> 11:47.438
♪ Come my lady ♪

11:47.521 --> 11:49.521
♪ You're my butterfly, sugar… ♪

11:51.105 --> 11:52.105
[White Rabbit sighs]

11:52.938 --> 11:53.771
Kill her.

12:04.855 --> 12:06.855
[frenetic industrial music spiking]

12:14.938 --> 12:16.188
[rocket launcher cocks]

12:16.271 --> 12:17.271
Anyone else?

12:20.063 --> 12:21.938
All right, everyone else.

12:26.938 --> 12:27.938
[gasps]

12:28.521 --> 12:29.396
[grunting]

12:42.105 --> 12:43.605
[panting]

12:53.855 --> 12:54.855
[trigger clicking]

12:55.896 --> 12:56.896
[grunts]

12:58.938 --> 12:59.896
[guns trill]

13:04.188 --> 13:05.438
[grunts]

13:07.980 --> 13:11.146
A formula I developed
based on Echidna's natural toxin.

13:11.730 --> 13:15.188
It won't kill you,
only paralyze you for a while.

13:15.271 --> 13:17.646
All of my warriors' blades
are doused with it.

13:17.730 --> 13:21.355
It'll give us plenty of time
to extract Dante's blood from him.

13:22.730 --> 13:25.271
We just have to land one blow.

13:25.771 --> 13:29.230
I do regret that you won't
be getting what you deserve,

13:29.896 --> 13:32.313
since you'll feel no pain as you die.

13:33.521 --> 13:34.521
Oh, well.

13:34.605 --> 13:36.605
[tense, drawn-out music intensifying]

13:40.646 --> 13:42.896
[rowdy, swaggering techno music plays]

13:49.355 --> 13:52.063
Yeah, and I've got some bad news.

13:52.146 --> 13:55.188
You didn't get that callback
for the Chuck E. Cheese band auditions.

13:55.271 --> 13:58.021
Dante! You made it.

14:01.980 --> 14:03.313
[Mary struggling]

14:03.396 --> 14:04.938
Before we start,

14:05.021 --> 14:08.146
let me at least show you
what you're fighting for.

14:12.396 --> 14:13.646
Is that…?

14:13.730 --> 14:15.730
Your father's homeland,

14:15.813 --> 14:19.521
where Mundus, the king who had
your family murdered, still rules.

14:21.146 --> 14:22.938
Fitting of Fate's dark humor,

14:23.021 --> 14:26.146
it was Mundus who gained the most
from Sparda's wall.

14:26.230 --> 14:31.021
It has allowed him to bleed dry
a captive, terrorized populace,

14:31.105 --> 14:34.313
while she and the rest
of her DARKCOM barbarians

14:34.396 --> 14:37.938
ensure Paradise
stays sealed off for their own kind.

14:38.021 --> 14:42.438
They and Mundus are two sides
of the same blood-stained coin.

14:42.521 --> 14:43.480
[Dante laughs]

14:43.563 --> 14:45.480
I'm sorry, but Paradise?

14:45.980 --> 14:47.771
You call this world Paradise?

14:47.855 --> 14:51.355
Compared to my world, yes.

14:52.188 --> 14:54.730
Come with me and see for yourself.

14:56.980 --> 14:57.980
[music trails off]

14:59.230 --> 15:02.313
Your dad was a brave warrior.

15:02.855 --> 15:04.230
But wherever he is,

15:04.313 --> 15:07.730
I know he's still fighting
to keep us safe.

15:09.521 --> 15:13.355
Anyone touches her in this world,
then you'll die in that one.

15:13.438 --> 15:15.105
Hands off the lieutenant!

15:15.730 --> 15:16.896
That's an order.

15:18.771 --> 15:21.146
[tense, eerie music playing]

15:29.813 --> 15:30.980
[Dante gasps]

15:33.230 --> 15:34.980
[thunder booms]

15:36.313 --> 15:38.188
[gags, coughs]

15:41.146 --> 15:44.646
A scorched earth,
and air turned to poison.

15:45.230 --> 15:48.105
Centuries' worth of devastation,

15:48.605 --> 15:54.855
wrought by tyrants who make
sapien stories of the devil seem quaint.

16:01.021 --> 16:04.646
Look and see
your father's wall for what it is.

16:04.730 --> 16:09.313
An artificial construct
raised by a man with immense power

16:09.396 --> 16:13.271
to do what all such constructs
are designed to do.

16:15.355 --> 16:18.021
Keep the powerless in their place.

16:22.813 --> 16:25.563
I created this device
to detect and prolong

16:25.646 --> 16:29.021
the random tears
that naturally appear in the wall.

16:29.105 --> 16:31.771
It's let me save handfuls of refugees.

16:32.521 --> 16:34.813
But with Makai's air in your lungs,

16:34.896 --> 16:38.771
you can understand
that will never be enough.

16:38.855 --> 16:43.396
The only true answer
is to let all Makaians cross over.

16:43.980 --> 16:46.980
Now, the wall must be destroyed.

16:47.896 --> 16:51.105
[struggling]
You're… You're talking about genocide.

16:51.188 --> 16:53.480
If every demon can cross into this world,

16:53.563 --> 16:55.563
humans won't stand a chance.

16:55.646 --> 16:57.021
Millions will die.

16:57.105 --> 16:59.438
You aren't listening.

16:59.521 --> 17:01.396
Millions already die.

17:01.938 --> 17:03.188
Yes, with the wall gone,

17:03.271 --> 17:06.605
the monsters of Makai will
come through along with the oppressed.

17:06.688 --> 17:08.021
But in its wake,

17:08.105 --> 17:12.896
the worlds will reach
a new, rebalanced equilibrium.

17:12.980 --> 17:15.605
What's the sacrifice of
a generation or two if it means

17:15.688 --> 17:19.230
ending suffering for those who come after?

17:19.313 --> 17:23.605
You can right
your father's injustice, Dante.

17:23.688 --> 17:26.896
It takes only a drop of your blood.

17:26.980 --> 17:28.771
My father was a hero.

17:28.855 --> 17:30.896
And how would you know that?

17:30.980 --> 17:34.396
All the deep, meaningful moments
you had together?

17:35.063 --> 17:36.313
[Mary groans]

17:36.396 --> 17:39.480
Don't… Don't be a fucking idiot!

17:39.563 --> 17:41.355
Do I have to shoot you again?

17:42.146 --> 17:43.730
She makes a compelling point.

17:44.230 --> 17:45.730
I'm gonna have to go with

17:45.813 --> 17:48.313
the not-murdering-all-of-humanity
side on this one.

17:50.355 --> 17:54.188
Then I guess we'll have to get
your blood out the traditional way!

17:54.271 --> 17:56.771
Careful, their blades are poisoned!

17:57.480 --> 17:59.980
Good thing none of them
are gonna touch me then.

18:00.063 --> 18:00.980
Let's rock.

18:01.480 --> 18:02.980
[raucous metal music playing]

18:04.313 --> 18:05.771
[Dante grunting]

18:19.646 --> 18:20.563
[energy pulses]

18:23.855 --> 18:26.855
Son of Sparda.

18:26.938 --> 18:30.563
Son of… a really ugly guy
with a weird thing for bats?

18:31.980 --> 18:33.105
[Dante gasps]

18:36.105 --> 18:38.355
[raucous metal music continuing]

18:46.771 --> 18:47.688
Commander!

18:48.813 --> 18:50.688
[demons, Dante gasping]

18:50.771 --> 18:52.646
[Dante] Harsh, but fair.

18:52.730 --> 18:54.146
You'll fight better this way.

19:21.646 --> 19:24.646
A drop of blood! I just need a drop!

19:24.730 --> 19:25.646
[Mary groaning]

19:28.188 --> 19:30.438
[frenetic techno music playing]

20:04.938 --> 20:09.105
So, how come none of you guys get cool
Alice in Wonderland-themed identities?

20:11.396 --> 20:14.355
I bet you'd really fill out
a nice Queen of Hearts dress!

20:18.063 --> 20:19.146
[gun trills]

20:20.146 --> 20:21.146
[White Rabbit] Hmm?

20:21.813 --> 20:23.230
Lady!

20:23.313 --> 20:24.980
[Mary grunts]

20:32.688 --> 20:34.688
Go! I can handle the sapien.

20:36.271 --> 20:39.021
It appears the dosage
wasn't quite strong enough,

20:39.105 --> 20:41.646
but let's focus on the positive.

20:41.730 --> 20:46.105
Maybe you will get to feel
the cold grip of death take you!

20:46.605 --> 20:47.438
[Mary grunts]

20:47.521 --> 20:48.980
You're so full of shit.

20:49.771 --> 20:51.938
I saw your DARKCOM hate shrine.

20:52.438 --> 20:54.813
-That's what you really care about.
-[seethes]

20:54.896 --> 20:58.771
If you were fighting for the oppressed,
you wouldn't be holding them prisoner.

21:00.271 --> 21:04.688
I feel every bit of pain
that I cause for my people.

21:05.271 --> 21:09.438
But how much crueler a fate
would they have met at your hands?

21:10.230 --> 21:16.063
I adopted the methods I was forced to
by an enemy willing to do worse.

21:16.146 --> 21:20.730
[Mary] DARKCOM isn't abusing orphans
to turn them into brainwashed soldiers.

21:20.813 --> 21:21.646
Really?

21:22.230 --> 21:24.771
Is that not
how you would describe yourself?

21:25.938 --> 21:29.563
Why did you think DARKCOM recruited you?

21:30.313 --> 21:34.563
Only those who have lost
all connection to their world

21:34.646 --> 21:37.938
are truly free
to fight for a different one.

21:38.521 --> 21:42.396
It is no coincidence
that our whole little unholy trinity

21:42.480 --> 21:44.938
had our families taken from us.

21:47.105 --> 21:50.771
Dante, you and I.

21:54.563 --> 21:55.813
[Mary gasps]

21:55.896 --> 21:58.438
["Afterlife" by Alex Seaver
and Amy Lee playing]

21:58.521 --> 21:59.771
[moody goth rock playing]

21:59.855 --> 22:02.105
[blood pumping steadily]

22:04.188 --> 22:09.021
I am your masterpiece, Lieutenant Arkham.

22:09.105 --> 22:13.938
♪ I'm all out of tears to cry ♪

22:14.021 --> 22:19.313
♪ Today, I'm not afraid to die… ♪

22:19.396 --> 22:21.063
That's impossible.

22:22.771 --> 22:24.063
You survived.

22:24.813 --> 22:26.646
[rowdy industrial metal playing]

22:40.605 --> 22:41.688
[guns clicking]

22:51.105 --> 22:52.105
[confused clamoring]

22:54.188 --> 22:56.021
[panicked clamoring]

23:00.980 --> 23:02.980
[Dante panting]

23:09.938 --> 23:13.480
You die here, in our world.

23:13.980 --> 23:15.688
-[snarls]
-[energy thrumming]

23:15.771 --> 23:16.771
[muffled grunt]

23:18.355 --> 23:22.396
[White Rabbit]
You and your team left me crippled,

23:22.480 --> 23:25.938
barely able to keep myself alive.

23:26.021 --> 23:29.146
Now I require a constant transfusion

23:29.230 --> 23:33.438
of this cocktail of demon blood
with its healing abilities

23:33.521 --> 23:36.230
to buy myself the time I need

23:36.980 --> 23:43.855
to destroy every piece of architecture
of injustice that killed my family.

23:43.938 --> 23:46.730
We didn't do… this.

23:47.605 --> 23:50.563
You were trying to help demons that night,

23:50.646 --> 23:51.980
but now…

23:52.063 --> 23:54.646
I should have known
you were human from the start.

23:54.730 --> 23:57.980
Your brand of pure,
psychotic ruthlessness?

23:58.605 --> 24:01.063
That's all humanity.

24:02.730 --> 24:04.980
On that, we agree.

24:06.771 --> 24:08.771
[frenzied industrial metal playing]

24:17.771 --> 24:18.771
[gasps deeply]

24:29.855 --> 24:31.063
[Dante straining]

24:40.688 --> 24:42.021
[energy crackling]

24:48.980 --> 24:50.605
How does this thing work?

24:50.688 --> 24:51.605
Uh…

24:51.688 --> 24:53.271
Do you just…

24:57.230 --> 24:58.396
[high-pitched ringing]

25:12.230 --> 25:16.313
Whoo! That was crazy!
Too bad your eyes weren't here to see it.

25:16.396 --> 25:18.563
[White Rabbit] One way or another,

25:20.105 --> 25:22.105
you are going to bleed.

25:23.105 --> 25:24.813
You're human.

25:25.396 --> 25:26.396
[White Rabbit grunts]

25:27.438 --> 25:29.605
[growling]

25:39.855 --> 25:41.146
[bellows]

25:56.688 --> 25:58.605
[Dante] You were never a demon at all.

25:58.688 --> 26:02.896
Just a man wearing a screwed-up bunny mask
to hide an even more screwed-up human face

26:02.980 --> 26:05.480
that has a bunch of weird tubes
sticking out of it.

26:05.563 --> 26:08.063
To be fair, I can see
why no one considered that.

26:08.146 --> 26:10.396
[labored breathing]

26:10.480 --> 26:12.646
I gave you the chance to end this.

26:13.896 --> 26:15.355
[ragged panting]

26:15.438 --> 26:17.230
I want you to remember that.

26:19.355 --> 26:22.021
When what will happen next happens,

26:22.605 --> 26:24.980
I want you to remember…

26:26.396 --> 26:28.230
that you could have stopped it.

26:29.188 --> 26:30.021
What do you me--

26:31.355 --> 26:32.855
[dark, brooding music playing]

26:45.688 --> 26:46.688
[Mary grunts]

26:47.438 --> 26:50.563
I guess you got
your mom's necklace back after all.

26:54.688 --> 26:55.605
Yeah.

26:56.688 --> 26:58.688
[helicopter blades whirring overhead]

27:04.146 --> 27:05.855
Hey, Dante!

27:05.938 --> 27:09.813
Your buddy Enzo
brought the cavalry for ya! Ha!

27:09.896 --> 27:14.730
I mean, they actually brought me
as a prisoner, but in spirit!

27:14.813 --> 27:16.396
Huh?

27:19.313 --> 27:21.063
What the hell happened here?

27:22.563 --> 27:25.063
Our first strike in the Holy War.

27:26.521 --> 27:28.480
The first of many to come.

27:35.105 --> 27:36.105
["Devils Never Cry" plays]

27:36.188 --> 27:37.563
♪ Bless me ♪

27:37.646 --> 27:43.646
♪ With the leaf off of the tree ♪

27:43.730 --> 27:47.563
♪ On it, I see ♪

27:47.646 --> 27:51.521
♪ The freedom reign ♪

27:51.605 --> 27:55.396
♪ We are falling ♪

27:55.480 --> 27:59.230
♪ The light is calling ♪

27:59.313 --> 28:03.146
♪ Tears inside me ♪

28:03.230 --> 28:07.105
♪ Calm me down ♪

28:07.188 --> 28:10.896
♪ Midnight calling ♪

28:10.980 --> 28:14.813
♪ Mist of resolving ♪

28:14.896 --> 28:16.855
♪ Crown me ♪

28:16.938 --> 28:22.688
♪ With the pure, green leaf ♪

28:22.771 --> 28:26.563
♪ Praise to my father ♪

28:26.646 --> 28:30.480
♪ Blessed by the water ♪

28:30.563 --> 28:34.396
♪ Black light, dark sky ♪

28:34.480 --> 28:36.105
IN MEMORY OF KEVIN CONROY (1955-2022)

28:36.188 --> 28:39.313
♪ The devil's cry ♪